definition.value: An oxo carboxylic acid that is propanal substituted by a carboxyethoxy group at position 2.
A member of the class of azetidines that is propylazetidine substituted by a 3-pyridyl group position 2 and a 4-toluenesulfonamido group at position 3.
An acetate ester that is ethyl acetate substituted by a pentyloxy group at position 2.
A dieter that is 1-pentoxyethane substituted by an ethoxy group at position 1.
An  imidazolidinone that is parabanic acid substituted by a 2-phenylethyl group at position 1.
An olefinic compound that is butanal substituted by a methyl group at position 3 and a [(1Z)-prop-1-en-1-yl]oxy group at position 4 respectively.
A dieter obtained by the forma condensation of the two carboxy groups of succinic acid with ethanol and 3-methylbutanol respectively.
A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-cholest-8-en-3beta-ol carrying carboxy and methyl substituents at position 4.
A dieter obtained by the formal condensation of the two carboxy groups of dimethylmalonic acid with ethanol and 2-phenylethanol respectively.
A 3beta-sterol that is ergosterol having an additional double bond at position 14.
An acetate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (acetyloxy)acetic acid with 2-methylbutanol.
An acetate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of 3-(methylsulfanyl)propan-1-ol with acetic acid.
A carboxylic ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of  succinic semialdehyde  with ethanol.

A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1H-imidazole which is substituted at positions 1, 4, and 5 by cyclohexyl, p-fluorophenyl, and 2-aminopyrimidin-4-yl groups, respectively. It is a selective inhibitor of the delta- and epsilon-isoforms of casein kinase 1 (CK1delta and CK1epsilon).
An ammonium ion resulting from the addition of two protons to the free base of PF-670462.
A phosphonic ester obtained by the esterification of both the hydroxy groups of butylphosphonic acid with ethanol and 2-phenylethanol respectively.
A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by a 2-ethoxy-1-methoxyethyl group at position 2.
A 3beta-sterol that consists of 4beta-methylzymosterol in which the 4alpha-hydrogen is replaced by a formyl group.
An alkadiene that is 1,5-octadiene substituted by an ethyl group at position 3.
A 3beta-sterol that consists of 4beta-methylzymosterol in which the 4alpha-hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxymethyl group.
A member of the class of cyclopentanes that is cyclopentane substituted by a 1-methylbutyl group.
A fatty acid ester obtained by the formal condensation of butan-1-ol with caproleic acid.
An alpha-diketone that is 1-phenyl-1,2-propanedione substituted by two methoxy groups at position 3.
A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-cholest-8-en-3beta-ol carrying an additional carboxy substituent at position 4alpha.
An acetate ester that is propyl acetate substituted by an ethoxy group at position 3.
A diester obtained by the formal condensation of both the carboxy groups of 2-hydroxyglutaric acid with two molecules of ethanol respectively.
A butan-4-olide that is gamma-butanolactone substituted by a 1-hydroxyethyl group at position 4.
An organoselenium compound  obtained by the formal condensation of butane-1-selenol with pentanoic acid.
An ortho-fused bicyclic hydrocarbon that is 1,2-dihydronaphthalene substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 1 and 5 respectively.
The fatty acid ethyl ester of 5-hexenoic acid.
A glucosylglycerol phosphate consisting of sn-glycerol 3-phosphate having an alpha-D-glucosyl residue attached at position 2.
An aldehyde that is thiophene substituted by a formyl group at position 2.
derivative of glyburide (CHEBI:5441), also known as azidoglibenclamide
A fatty acid ethyl ester obtained by the formal condensation of isobutyric acid with ethanol.
A member of the class of azulenes that is azulene substituted by methyl groups at positions 4, 6 and 8 respectively.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-trans-feruloyl-CoA. Major structure at pH 7.3.
A ketoaldonic acid obtained by oxidation of the 8-hydroxy group of 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosonic acid to the corresponding aldehyde.
A butan-4-olide that is gamma-butyrolactone substituted by an ethoxy group at position 5.
A member of the class of oxolanes that is oxolane (tetrahydrofuran) substituted by a dichloromethyl group at position 2.
A ketone that is decane in which the methylene hydrogens at position 3 are replaced by an oxo group.
A primary alcohol that is butan-1-ol substituted by a chloro group at position 4.
A secondary alcohol that is tridecane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7.
A fatty acid ethyl ester obtained by the formal condensation of 3-nonenoic acid with ethanol.
An amino monosaccharide obtained by replacement of the 8-hydroxy group of 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulopyranosonic acid by an amino group.
A member of the class of acetophenones that is acetophenone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 2 respectively.
An alkene that is decane containing one double bond at position 1.
An  aminonaphthalenesulfonic acid that is 2-naphthalenesulfonic acid substituted by an amino group at position 7 and a hydroxy group at position 4 respectively.
A dioxolane that is 1,3-dioxolane substituted by an isopropyl group at position 2.
